# Sensitive paths require platform-team review.
# This is one of the layers protecting prod from accidental or deliberate bypass.
# See docs/PROD_LOCKDOWN.md for the full enforcement model.

# Deploy + CI machinery: the only path to prod
/.github/workflows/                  {{.github_codeowners_team}}
/.github/CODEOWNERS                  {{.github_codeowners_team}}
/scripts/                            {{.github_codeowners_team}}

# Bundle + resource bindings: change these and you change prod
/databricks.yml                      {{.github_codeowners_team}}
/app.yaml                            {{.github_codeowners_team}}
/permissions.yaml                    {{.github_codeowners_team}}

# Schema changes: irreversible if downgrade is bad
/migrations/                         {{.github_codeowners_team}}
/alembic.ini                         {{.github_codeowners_team}}

# Governance documents
/docs/ARCHITECTURE.md                {{.github_codeowners_team}}
/docs/DATA_CLASSIFICATION.md         {{.github_codeowners_team}}
/docs/PROD_LOCKDOWN.md               {{.github_codeowners_team}}
/.claude/CLAUDE.md                   {{.github_codeowners_team}}

# Everything else (routes, UI, business logic) is fair game for any developer.
